# Second argument slide
A UNIX/NeXT/FreeBSD base:
- OS X was first based off of System 9 and NeXTSTEP
    - NeXTSTEP was a UNIX based OS originally developed in the late 80's early 90's
- Most Userland utilities and the C library on OS X are derived from FreeBSD
- XNU kernel for OS X includes older version of FreeBSD subsystems



