# Third argument slide
Security:
- OS X isn't invincible, but it does a damn good job 
    - only ~120 viruses (2012)
- Adopts Rich security benefits from having a UNIX/FreeBSD base
- Most crackers target Windows™
    - There are about 60,000 viruses known for Windows™ (in 2003)

